                            <comment id="15398" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 13 Nov 2005 09:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AbstractApplicationContext registers a ClassLoader-aware ClassEditor for its configured ClassLoader now. Furthermore, I&apos;ve revised the entire ClassLoader handling to determine a default ClassLoader at construction time, if appropriate, instead of obtaining the thread context ClassLoader on actual access (which causes known issues with JMX and RMI requests which do not necessarily have the expected thread context ClassLoader).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57990" author="ittayd" created="Mon, 13 Sep 2010 11:36:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ResourceEditorRegistrar registers ClassEditor with the right class loader. However, it doesn&apos;t register ClassArrayEditor. So the problem in the bug exists for properties of type Class[]&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57991" author="ittayd" created="Mon, 13 Sep 2010 11:36:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;in 3.0.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="58025" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 13 Sep 2010 22:58:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good catch - that gap has been closed for 3.0.5 now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
